LAGOS – A Niger Delta-based human rights group, Centre for Human Rights and Anti-Corruption (CHURAC), has threatened to challenge the recent appointment of a Sole Administrator for the Niger Delta Development Commission (NDDC) in court. Barrister Alaowei E. Cleric, CHURAC National President, in a statement issued on Wednesday, described the appointment of Sole Administrator to manage the affairs of the NDDC as unlawful and should not be allowed. He stated that there was nowhere in the NDDC Establishment Act that provided for the position of Sole Administrator, stressing that such action was illegal, describing it as a gateway to continue the sleaze in the commission. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! He said: “Sen. Godswill Akpabio, the minister of the Niger Delta, should not turn NDDC to his personal property. We will not watch akimbo and allow some corrupt minds to pilfer away our common patrimony.” According to him, “The ongoing forensic audit is another scam. It has only provided a platform for looting of the commission’s scarce resources. What made Sen. Akpabio to think that the forensic auditors cannot do the work under a substantive board?” Kanu’s Militia May Worsen Insecurity In S’East – Group Appointment Of Sole Administrator For NNPC Is Illegal, Will Encourage Looting – Kalu Cleric called on President Muhammadu Buhari not to allow his office to be manipulated by those he termed pen robbers, stressing that his actions and inactions towards the NDDC crisis amounted to trading with the peace in the Niger Delta. “Mr. President should immediately disband that illegal and unlawful Sole Administrator and appoint a substantive board in line with the commission’s enabling Act. “The president should act fast to reverse his illegal decision on the appointment of Sole Administrator in NDDC, or we shall seek judicial inte